tunneled cuffed catheter, 6 with an arteriovenous fistula, and 2 with an 
arteriovenous graft. Three patients regained renal function after an average 112 
days and one was lost to follow-up. Of the 33 remaining on HD, 8 required 
nursing home admission and 25 were discharged home after initiating HD. Among 
these 33, 19 died and 14 remained on HD at the end of study period. Days on 
dialysis (mean ± SEM) before death in those discharged to a nursing facility 
versus home were 52.6 ± 14.7 versus 386.1 ± 90.7 (P < 0.05), respectively.
